President Barack Obama has announced his intent to nominate William E. Spriggs as Assistant Secretary for Policy at the Department of Labor, and Rebecca M. Blank as Under Secretary for Economics Affairs at the Department of Commerce. Spriggs is currently a professor and Chair of the Department of Economics at Howard University, and has held various positions in government service during the Clinton Administration. Blank is currently a Senior Fellow at the Brookings Institution, and has served as a Member of the President's Council of Economic Advisers. Her research focuses on the interactions between the macroeconomy, government policy, and the behavior and well-being of American families.